# Native audio module contract (iOS)

Apply when editing native audio code, the JS adapter (lib/playerAdapter.ts), or any code that assumes how the player or events work.

## Platform

- Playback is implemented only on **iOS** (`modules/yhwav-audio`).
- The adapter checks `isAvailable()` and uses the module only on iOS; no Android implementation in this module.

## Player

- `AVQueuePlayer` in `YhwavAudioModule.swift`.
- Queue is tracked via `trackOrder` (ids) and `trackMetadata`; `skip(index)` rebuilds/repositions the queue.

## Events

Native sends: `PlaybackProgressUpdated`, `PlaybackQueueEnded`, `PlaybackActiveTrackChanged`, `RemotePlay`/`RemotePause`/`RemoteNext`/`RemotePrevious`/`RemoteSeek`, `AudioLevelsUpdated`.

- **PlaybackError** is declared but never emitted in the current native code; do not rely on it.

## Buffering

- There is no separate "Buffering" event.
- Buffering is reported as `state === "buffering"` when `timeControlStatus == .waitingToPlayAtSpecifiedRate` inside `getPlaybackState()`.
- JS gets this via `usePlaybackState()` (subscribes to progress and calls `getPlaybackState()`).

## Gapless

- Gapless behavior comes from AVQueuePlayer (next item already in queue).
- No explicit preload in the active native module.
- JS prewarm (Range fetch on next track URL when &lt; 45s left) is in useAudioStore only.

## Bridge

- All `TrackPlayer.*` methods in `lib/playerAdapter.ts` map directly to the native module.
- `useTrackPlayerEvents` maps native event names to internal `Event.*` and passes through `index`, `position`, `duration` where applicable.
